The paper deals with machine learning tasks, specifically learning from conditional distributions, which is a common problem in several subfields of computer science. The paper proposes a novel approach and algorithm to address this problem, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in the areas of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and control systems (cs.SY).
